-- Argentina’s Badlar Falls Below 12% for First Time Since July
-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 2012-05-02T21:00:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-02/argentina-s-badlar-falls-below-12-for-first-time-since-july.html
Argentina ’s benchmark deposit rate,
known as the  badlar , fell to less than 12 percent for the first
time since July.  The badlar, the interest rate paid on 30-day deposits of
more than 1 million pesos ($226 million), sank to 11.81 percent
on April 26, the central bank said in a statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in Buenos Aires at 
